<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[227,773,1617,1679]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<heading box="[227,773,1617,1647]" centered="true" fontSize="12" level="2" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" reason="2">
3.2.1 Diversity and systematics of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MOTSCHULSKY" authorityYear="1858" box="[616,745,1617,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[616,745,1617,1647]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Orphnebius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in
</heading>
<heading box="[227,692,1649,1679]" fontSize="13" level="1" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" reason="1">the East Palaearctic and Oriental regions</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,795,1705,2082]" lastBlockId="2.[832,1437,233,738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
The East Palaearctic and Oriental 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MOTSCHULSKY" authorityYear="1858" box="[574,696,1705,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[574,696,1705,1729]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Orphnebius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fauna is currently represented by 175 species, at least 13 of them of doubtful identity. In the majority of species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="EPPELSHEIM" authorityYear="1895" box="[686,793,1769,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hauseri">
<emphasis box="[686,793,1769,1793]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">O. hauseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group), the male sexual characters are crucial for a positive identification at the species level; the spermatheca may be suitable for an identification of the respective subgroup, but is insufficient for the diagnosis of species. For more details see 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[433,604,1929,1953]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="13 - 111" refId="ref33270" refString="ASSING, V. 2016 b: On some Lomechusini of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Contributions to Entomology 66 (1): 13 - 111 - DOI: 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 66.1.013 - 111." type="journal article" year="2016">ASSING (2016b)</bibRefCitation>
. Two main lineages are identified within Palaearctic and Oriental 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MOTSCHULSKY" authorityYear="1858" box="[189,311,1993,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,311,1993,2017]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Orphnebius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The more speciose of them is the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="EPPELSHEIM" authorityYear="1895" box="[686,793,1993,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hauseri">
<emphasis box="[686,793,1993,2017]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">O. hauseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (76 species), which again is composed of several subgroups (
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[322,476,2057,2081]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="13 - 111" refId="ref33270" refString="ASSING, V. 2016 b: On some Lomechusini of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Contributions to Entomology 66 (1): 13 - 111 - DOI: 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 66.1.013 - 111." type="journal article" year="2016">ASSING 2016b</bibRefCitation>
). At some point, this group name will be replaced by one of the existing subgeneric names proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="BERNHAUER, M." box="[1044,1253,265,289]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="142 - 155" refId="ref33427" refString="BERNHAUER, M. 1929: Zur Kenntnis der Gattungen Astilbus STEPH., Orphnebius MOTSCH. und Deroleptus BERNH. - Zoologischer Anzeiger 82: 142 - 155." type="journal article" year="1929">BERNHAUER (1929)</bibRefCitation>
. However, not all of the 
<typeStatus box="[900,946,298,322]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">type</typeStatus>
species of these names have been revised yet; for a discussion of the problem see 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[1213,1384,329,353]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="13 - 111" refId="ref33270" refString="ASSING, V. 2016 b: On some Lomechusini of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Contributions to Entomology 66 (1): 13 - 111 - DOI: 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 66.1.013 - 111." type="journal article" year="2016">ASSING (2016b)</bibRefCitation>
. The second lineage is formed by the species now assigned to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1915" box="[939,1051,393,417]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deroleptus">
<emphasis box="[939,1051,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Deroleptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(69 species), which can be divided into three sub-lineages (for details see 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[1272,1425,425,449]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" pagination="13 - 111" refId="ref33270" refString="ASSING, V. 2016 b: On some Lomechusini of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Contributions to Entomology 66 (1): 13 - 111 - DOI: 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 66.1.013 - 111." type="journal article" year="2016">ASSING 2016b</bibRefCitation>
), the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2010" box="[885,974,457,481]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="draco">
<emphasis box="[885,974,457,481]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">O. draco</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (3 species), the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="CAMERON" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[1270,1352,457,481]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niger">
<emphasis box="[1270,1352,457,481]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">O. niger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (18 species), and the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="CAMERON" authorityYear="1939" box="[1068,1221,489,513]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siwalikensis">
<emphasis box="[1068,1221,489,513]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">O. siwalikensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (35 species). The subgroup affiliations of the remaining 13 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1915" box="[1324,1436,521,545]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deroleptus">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,521,545]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Deroleptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species is unclear, as they have not been revised and their respective original descriptions are insufficient for a positive assignment. The same is true of the species listed as 
<taxonomicName authority="Assing, 2017" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2017" box="[832,954,649,673]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="incertae sedis">
<emphasis box="[832,954,649,673]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Orphnebius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[962,1109,649,673]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">incertae sedis</taxonomicNameLabel>
(30 species). They need to be revised in order to attribute them to either the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="EPPELSHEIM" authorityYear="1895" box="[1328,1436,681,705]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hauseri">
<emphasis box="[1328,1436,681,705]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">O. hauseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1915" box="[930,1042,713,737]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orphnebius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Deroleptus">
<emphasis box="[930,1042,713,737]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Deroleptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(and the respective subgroups).
</paragraph>
